(9. Safety, Ethics, and Privacy) Tj
T*
(- JWT authentication and role-based access) Tj
T*
(- Clear disclaimers about AI limitations) Tj
T*
(- No external AI providers, reduced data exposure) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(10. Accessibility and Inclusion) Tj
T*
(- Low-bandwidth mode) Tj
T*
(- Voice guidance support) Tj
T*
(- Multilingual UI options) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(11. Limitations) Tj
T*
(- Model trained on synthetic data for demo purposes) Tj
T*
(- Rule-based chatbot is not diagnostic) Tj
T*
(- Real-world deployment requires clinical validation) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(12. Future Work) Tj
T*
(- Integrate real clinical datasets) Tj
T*
(- Add offline caching) Tj
T*
(- Expand emergency integrations with local services) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(13. Hackathon Jury Q and A \(Prepared\)) Tj
T*
(Q1: What problem are you solving?) Tj
T*
(A: Delayed diagnosis and limited access in rural healthcare.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q2: Why not just telemedicine?) Tj
T*
(A: We combine triage, explanation, emergency workflows, and booking in one platform.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q3: How safe is the AI?) Tj
T*
(A: It is decision support only, with clear disclaimers and escalation paths.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q4: Why RandomForest?) Tj
T*
(A: Robust for structured data, interpretable, reliable baseline.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q5: How do you handle free-text symptoms?) Tj
T*
(A: Rule-based and fuzzy matching, no paid NLP APIs.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q6: What if AI service is down?) Tj
T*
(A: Backend has fallbacks and UI gracefully handles errors.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q7: How is data protected?) Tj
T*
(A: JWT auth, role-based access, no external AI calls.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q8: How do you scale?) Tj
T*
(A: AI is a separate service, backend is stateless, easy to scale horizontally.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q9: What is unique here?) Tj
T*
(A: Integrated triage + emergency response + consultation + explanation.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q10: What are the next steps?) Tj
T*
(A: Clinical validation and integration with real health systems.) Tj
T*
